   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/> Diis Manibus.
                <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen" key="Caius">
                     <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Poppaeus">Poppaeus</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Vales">Vales</name>
               </persName> et
                <lb n="3"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Poppaea">Poppaea</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Ilias">Ilias</name>
               </persName> fecerunt
                <lb n="4"/>sibi et <persName>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Aviania">Avianiae</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Charis">Charidi</name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="5"/>amicae suae carissimae.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>To the divine shades. Gaius Poppaeus Vales and Poppaea Ilias made (this monument) for themselves and for Aviania Charis, (their) dearest friend.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The Penn Museum webpage suggests that this epitaph was, at some point in time, "mended" with another inscription in their collection (accession number L-1033-28B).</p>
         </div>
